#. type: Content of: <chapter><section><section><para>
#: en/installation-and-basic-configuration.xml:244
#| msgid "<emphasis>Script 3.4. Firsts steps to install OTRS.</emphasis>"
msgid "<emphasis>Script 3.4. First steps to install OTRS.</emphasis>"
msgstr "<emphasis>Script 3.4. Установка OTRS, первые шаги.</emphasis>"

#. type: Content of: <chapter><section><section><para>
#: en/installation-and-basic-configuration.xml:248
#| msgid ""
#| "Because the modules of OTRS should not be executed with root rights, you "
#| "should add a new user for OTRS as the next step. The home directory of "
#| "this new user should be <filename>/opt/otrs</filename>. If your web "
#| "server is not running with the same user rights as the new otrs user, "
#| "which is the case on most systems, you have to add the new otrs user to "
#| "the group of the web server user (see Script 3.5 below)."
msgid "OTRS should NOT be run with root rights. You should add a new user for OTRS as the next step. The home directory of this new user should be <filename>/opt/otrs</filename>. If your web server is not running with the same user rights as the new 'otrs' user, which is the case on most systems, you have to add the new 'otrs' user to the group of the web server user (see Script 3.5 below)."
msgstr "OTRS не должен выполнятся с правами администратора (root rights). На следующем шаге установки для OTRS необходимо добавить нового пользователя. Домашняя директория нового пользователя должна находится в каталоге <filename>/opt/otrs</filename>.  Если веб-сервер не работает с теми правами что и новый пользователь 'otrs' (а именно так и есть в большинстве систем), то его нужно добавить в группу пользователей веб-сервера  (см ниже Сценарий 3.5 )."

#. type: Content of: <chapter><section><section><para><screen>
#: en/installation-and-basic-configuration.xml:254
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"linux:/opt# useradd -r -d /opt/otrs/ -c 'OTRS user' otrs\n"
"linux:/opt# usermod -G nogroup otrs\n"
"linux:/opt#\n"
msgstr ""
"linux:/opt# useradd -r -d /opt/otrs/ -c 'OTRS user' otrs\n"
"linux:/opt# usermod -G nogroup otrs\n"
"linux:/opt#\n"

#. type: Content of: <chapter><section><section><para>
#: en/installation-and-basic-configuration.xml:261
#| msgid ""
#| "<emphasis>Script 3.5. Adding a new user and adding it to a group.</"
#| "emphasis>"
msgid "<emphasis>Script 3.5. Adding a new user 'otrs', and adding it to a group.</emphasis>"
msgstr "<emphasis>Сценарий 3.5. Добавление нового пользователя 'otrs' и добавление его в группу.</emphasis>"

#. type: Content of: <chapter><section><section><para>
#: en/installation-and-basic-configuration.xml:265
#| msgid ""
#| "Now you have to copy some sample configuration files. The system will "
#| "later use the copied files. The files are located in <filename>/opt/otrs/"
#| "Kernel</filename> and <filename>/opt/otrs/Kernel/Config</filename> and "
#| "have the suffix .dist (see Script 3.6 below)."
